FBIS4-10316 "drlat070_a_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Signs Customs Accords With Goldenberg Signs Customs Accords With Goldenberg FL1204125494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 11 Apr 94 FL1204125494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Report by correspondent Roberto Cavada Barrera] [Excerpt] On 11 April, Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina ratified in Peru an antidrug trafficking agreement and a customs accord between Cuban and Peruvian customs services. Robaina and Peruvian Foreign Minister Efrain Goldenberg signed the agreements at the closing of an official meeting at the Torre Tagle Palace. The meeting between Robaina and Goldenberg, who is also Peru's prime minister, lasted 45 minutes. Goldenberg granted us an exclusive interview for Radio Rebelde's "Exclusive" program: [Begin recording] [Goldenberg] This is just one more step in the long friendship that unites Peru and Cuba. We are ready to engage in other issues and continue to make progress. [Cavada] Are you pleased with Foreign Minister Robaina's visit? [Goldenberg] Of course. [end recording] [passage omitted]
